Source:  Journal
Author:  TAYLOR
Vol / Page:  5/51
Edition:
Quote:  The mountains here [central NI] are very lofty and covered with an ochreous soil, the manoa principally grows on them it is a sacred shrub not used as fuel for cooking said to be te matamua o nga rakau and if burnt to cause rain.
